name: In tea
directions: The shop is next to town hall and the bathroom is in the back next to the more private seating
comment: This shop is also really good and everyone who works there is very nice.

name: Taco Bell
street: 1 block north of Broadway and Littleton blvd.
directions: on the right as you first walk in

name: Enchanted Grounds
directions: One men's stall, one women's stall, and one neutral stall in the the far back of the cafe, just past the comic books.
comment: You may want to browse a bit first, or grab a drink (which are all awesome). Super friendly environment!

name: Subway
directions: In the back, by the soda machine.
comment: I worked there for a year, and we never told anyone they couldn't use our bathroom. Hours are generally from 10AM-midnight, 7 days a week. Different hours or closed on holidays.

name: Tesla Service Center
directions: Inside the showroom area to the west are 2 bathrooms marked “unisex”
comment: It’s in an area where they have see real cars on display to check out, no issues with walking in and using the bathroom

name: Tattered Cover Bookstore
street: Aspen Grove, 7301 S Santa Fe Dr,  80120
directions: Three bathrooms located in the back left by YA Novel section

name: GoodTurn Cycles
directions: In the back past the workshop, on the right.

name: Music & Arts
directions: Back of store and to the left

name: Nixon's Coffee House
directions: Back of the shop, past the seating area.
comment: No signs that you have to be a paying customer. No changing tables, FTR.

name: South Metro Denver Realtor Association
directions: Gendered single stalls on first floor north side. Also full restrooms upstairs rarely used.
comment: Office space with visitors in and out everyday. Upstairs restrooms are gendered/multiuser but unoccupied 99% of the time. Close to bus stop.

name: Walmart super center
directions: All the way in the back of the store there are all gender bath rooms

name: King Soopers
directions: Behind Starbucks, back of store

name: Southwest Plaza Mall
directions: First floor in the children's play area.
comment: Great option for transgender kids.

name: Shell Gas Station
directions: In the back across from the register
comment: Clean, no mirror

name: Garbanzo Mediterranean Fresh
comment: Their bathroom signs specifically embrace nonbinary/trans folx: each sign has a male figure, a female figure, and one that shows 1/2 and 1/2.

name: STEM School and Academy
directions: In either of the offices.
comment: Ask the office people to go.

name: Starbucks
directions: There are two unisex, single stall restrooms next to each other

name: Cheesecake factory
directions: Restaurant is in the southwest plaza mall
comment: The staff is wonderfuly accepting and friendly

name: The Cheesecake Factory
directions: Right from the entrance
comment: Preferred paying customer

name: First Universalist Church Denver
comment: During business hours and on Sunday. Ring North door doorbell during the week and just let them know you need a gender neutral bathroom

name: Arapahoe Libraries - Koelbel Library
directions: First level, east side. Near young adult area of library
comment: Open to all

name: Koelbel Library
directions: First floor, straight back past the teen section in a little corridor on your left
comment: You don’t have to be a library card holder to use the restroom. No one will bother you.

name: First Universalist Church of Denver
directions: Through Friendship Hall to the right.
comment: If it's between 9-3pm weekdays, ring the north doorbell.

name: Dairy Queen
directions: Once stepping in walk to the back and to the right.
comment: Can go in with no problem.

name: Mona Lisa's Calzones & Pizza
directions: In the back
comment: The one on the right has a urinal, if it helps

name: Nagel dining hall
directions: Up the stairs by the Mexican food place, between the men and women's rooms

name: Grandma's House
directions: Two non-labelled rooms at the back right corner.
comment: Depending on how busy it is you could just walk right to it. The bar is to the left when you enter.

name: University of Denver Graduate School of Social Work
directions: Main floor has multi-stall gender-neutral bathroom and each floor has a single-stall gender neutral bathroom.

name: Anderson Academic Commons
directions: There are several single-stall bathrooms, all of which lock. All of them are on the northeast side of the building, and there is one on each floor.

name: Anderson Academic Commons
directions: Located on the east side of the bottom and upper levels, and on the south west side of the main level.

name: Anderson Academic Commons at University of Denver
directions: Gender neutral bathrooms are located on all three floors in the north east side of the building. The main floor bathroom is accessible.
comment: A map of the building can be found here: https://library.du.edu/maps/index.html Gender neutral bathrooms are currently marked with a white triangle inside a green circle.

name: Univ. of Denver Law School
directions: Every level of the library on the east wall.
comment: There are locking gendered bathrooms and  unisex, handicap accessible bathrooms.

name: Alternation Brewing Company
directions: In the back near the brewing vats

name: TRHS by auditorium
directions: Next to the auditorium
comment: Students and staff ONLY

name: Trhs library
directions: In the library near the conference room
comment: Students and staff ONLY

name: Floyd's 99 Barber Shop
comment: For customer use, but if you browse products it will look just fine, especially if the store is busy.

name: Ross-University Hills Library
directions: In the children's area on the east side of the building.

name: Joann Fabric
directions: Rear right corner, past fabric cutting table.
comment: Not sure about changing table, didn't go in.

name: Black Project Brewing
directions: Back of the taproom
comment: There's also a back entrance to the brewery that goes out to the alley

name: St Andrew UMC
directions: Main lobby by welcome desk - two unisex bathrooms
comment: Church is reconciling.  A very open, welcoming place for LGBTQ community.  So bathrooms are safe but so is the entire building.

name: Gender Identity Center
directions: Restroom is gender neutral
comment: Open 10 am to 9 pm Monday, Tuesday through Saturday, 10 am to 7 pm

name: Gender Identity Center
directions: All bathrooms are gender neutral.
comment: Anyone and everyone is welcome at any time.

name: Localhost Arena Lakewood
directions: In the long hallway that goes past the mega screen

name: ULTA Beauty
directions: All the way in the back on the left hand side around the corner just past the salon.
comment: Single stall gendered bathrooms but definitely used by either gender without question.

name: Denver Museum of Nature and Science
directions: Third floor to the right of the escalator right before the entrance to the temporary exhibits. Family restrooms also on the first floor just inside the Gems and Minerals Hall.

name: Agave
comment: Gender neutral single stall restroom for restaraunt patronns.

name: Honey Baked Ham
directions: Take a left when you walk through the door, it’s in a small hallway.
comment: Tell the employees that you are using the bathroom, they are friendly. You don’t have to buy anything, but we would prefer if you did.

name: Starbucks
directions: In the very back
comment: Can be busy in the morning, but even then the line is usually nonexistent.

name: Li'l Devils Lounge
directions: Back left corner of building.
comment: Women's restroom is single occupant with locking doors used by all genders of staff and patrons. This is a small neighborhood gay bar.

name: The Bardo Coffee House
directions: Straight back, to the right of the booths.
comment: You might need to buy something.

name: Blackbird Public House
directions: To the right on the west side of the bar

name: Lunchbox wax
comment: Staff is amazingly comforting and uses proper pronouns without prompts :)

name: Jamba Juice
directions: Walk straight inside
comment: I don’t think you have to buy anything...

name: Glacier Gelato
directions: Walk straight through to the back

name: Target at The Commons
street: The Commons At Federal Way, 2201 S Commons
directions: Look for the sign that says restrooms, its by the outdoor entrance/exit
comment: Target has a transgender bathroom policy that allows trans people to use the bathroom they are most comfortable with, whether it match their gender, sex, or its their family bathroom. If you're harassed bring it up with an employee. They also have a policy that protects breastfeeding mothers, so they are a generally safe place.

name: Target
directions: On the second floor next to the pharmacy.
comment: New store, clean facility.

name: Gender identity center
directions: Accessible to all. Great recourse and refuge. This is a Safe space.
comment: You need to sign in. Ask this is not technically a public restroom. You Need to be Gender variant identifying but CIs gender people who are accepting and supportive are also welcomed.

name: Nooch Vegan Market
directions: Just past the checkout, to the left.

name: Sol Tribe Custom Tattoo and Body Piercing
directions: Shared with Sweet Action Ice Cream, accessible through either shop.

name: Sol Tribe Custom Tattoo and Body Piercing
directions: Shared with Sweet Action Ice Cream, accessible through either shop.

name: Cherry Creek High School
directions: Across from IC cafe, two gender-neutral bathrooms.
comment: Sometimes one is locked by faculty. Another is always unlocked for student use.

name: Novel Strand Brewing Company
comment: POC owned and inclusive, at least one queer bartender. Bathrooms are fully gender neutral and accessible!

name: Punchbowl Social
directions: Front dining area, along the side of the kitchen.

name: 7 eleven
directions: To the right of the slushee machine

name: Nextdoor Glendale
directions: Behind hostess station on the right
comment: Paying customer (restaurant)

name: Bull & Bush
directions: Gender neutral restroom in bar near male and female restrooms.

name: The Wizards Chest Toy Store
directions: Two single stall bathrooms marked for make of female. Located in back of store on both levels.

name: Paintbrush Park
comment: Public park single unit, cement outhouse no sink /hand cleaner

name: Four Mile Historic Park
directions: Single stall are available on the park in the Bee House and Gate House buildings.
comment: The bathrooms in the main building Grant Hall, are not single stall but if you are in need of a safe restroom and unable to pay the admission to visit the park ask at the front desk and they will provide you access to a single stall restroom in the office area.

name: IKEA
directions: family restroom in the front, near the main entrance.

name: Whole Foods Market
directions: Two at far left of entrance.

name: Cherry Creek Mall
directions: Lower level, right next to the gendered ones.
comment: It's officially a family room.

name: Apple store
directions: Back of the store to the left
comment: You can literally use our bathroom anytime, just open the door at the back and pick whichever room you prefer. They are single toilet rooms.

name: Natural Grocers on East Alameda
directions: In the back right corner upon walking in. There are 3 private restrooms that are gender neutral.
comment: I’ve never had trouble just walking in and using them, I think it’s fine as long as nobody trashes anything

name: Denver Helth Medical Center
directions: Denver Heath campus is a gender accepting campus and allows people to use the restrooms of their gender identity

name: Ikea
directions: first floor up the escalator
comment: two family restrooms

name: Black Eye Coffee
directions: Ground level access, two unisex single stall bathrooms with locking doors

name: Park Meadows Mall, Food Court
directions: Immediately to left as you walk indoor to food court from outside. Down hall towards restrooms and you'll see it.

name: Park Meadows Mall
directions: Anywhere there is bathrooms located, you can find the family restroom.
comment: Depending on how busy the area is depends on whether you can get in. Remember there are several bathrooms pin pointed across the mall.

name: Whole Foods Market Belmar
directions: Far left of entrance.

name: Osage cafe
directions: In the Osage Cafe open to customers during business hours. The Building also has a Non public restroom that is Disabled accessible and Gender neutral on the secound floor. You must be a resident or Guest to access the community room.
comment: You have to be a paying customer. The secound floor is for building residents only. My extension is 043*

name: Wishing well enterprises
directions:
Open 9:00 am-5:00 pm consumers only. Must have ID. 
Mental health center of Denver community outreach center has two gender neutral bathrooms.
comment: Check in at the front desk. Entry is limited to people who use Denver entail health services. It does not hurt to ask leave you're ID.

name: East High
directions: There’s 2, one on the second floor in the back hallway, next to the science classrooms and the dance room. The other one is in the nurses office on the first floor, in the back hallway near the theatre Black Box and entry to backstage of the auditorium.
comment: You have to be a student or staff member to get into the building, but I know a lot of LGBT students didn’t know about these so I thought I’d put these on here :)

name: Strange Craft Beer Company
directions: One is immediately to the left of the bar, the other is a ways to the right through the barrel room
comment: Must be 21+

name: Temple Emanuel
directions: At the end of the hallway. Is wheelchair accessible.

name: Denver Art Museum
directions: Family restrooms on first and second floor of south Hamilton building, also on certain floors of North building
comment: First floor of Hamilton building may be accessible without ticket, but other floors do require admission

name: City o City
directions: Two gender neutral restrooms in back by bar
comment: Welcomed to all. Both restrooms have been made gender neutral in 2020.

name: The Denver Mint Gift Shop
directions: Gift shop is free. Restroom is to the left in a corner.

name: DIA Terminal B concourse
directions: Room 2361
comment: There is usually a single unisex bathroom with changing table in between each set of Men’s and Women’s in DIA Termal B

name: Ross Cherry Creek Library
directions: Second floor, past the public computer area, past the meeting rooms, in the corner.

name: Auraria Campus CCD Confluence,
directions: Next to elevators on each floor
comment: Only open during campus hours (weekdays)

name: Colorado state capitol
directions: Second floor on the north end on the right -- two single stall unisex bathrooms. 3rd floor on the NW side by the gallery -- unisex accessible bathroom. Other neutral bathrooms but those are the easiest to find.
comment: The Capitol can be intimidating but it's fully public, very safe, and full of other wandering visitors so don't worry.
